<p><span class="highlight" data-annotation="%7B%22attachmentURI%22%3A%22http%3A%2F%2Fzotero.org%2Fusers%2F11261961%2Fitems%2FK4FEFN2B%22%2C%22annotationKey%22%3A%227U5A7EHW%22%2C%22color%22%3A%22%23ffd400%22%2C%22pageLabel%22%3A%227%22%2C%22position%22%3A%7B%22pageIndex%22%3A6%2C%22rects%22%3A%5B%5B318.717%2C115.349%2C545.64%2C121.903%5D%2C%5B306.61%2C104.926%2C540.448%2C111.481%5D%2C%5B306.682%2C94.448%2C554.748%2C101.002%5D%2C%5B306.61%2C84.026%2C536.836%2C90.58%5D%2C%5B306.658%2C73.546%2C552.542%2C80.101%5D%5D%7D%2C%22citationItem%22%3A%7B%22uris%22%3A%5B%22http%3A%2F%2Fzotero.org%2Fusers%2F11261961%2Fitems%2F5N4VM3B9%22%5D%2C%22locator%22%3A%227%22%7D%7D">“Em sexto lugar, realizamos diferentes experimentos com algoritmos genéticos multiobjetivos até encontrarmos a solução mais viável. Czarn, MacNish, Vijayan, Turlach e Gupta (2004) exploraram alguns ajustes para parâmetros genéticos. Nesse sentido, aproveitamos o aprendizado de RNA e a otimização metaheurística de algoritmos genéticos multiobjetivos para encontrar a alocação do orçamento público.”</span></p>
