<p><span class="highlight" data-annotation="%7B%22attachmentURI%22%3A%22http%3A%2F%2Fzotero.org%2Fusers%2F11261961%2Fitems%2FK4FEFN2B%22%2C%22annotationKey%22%3A%22IIMSAI5K%22%2C%22color%22%3A%22%23ffd400%22%2C%22pageLabel%22%3A%2211%22%2C%22position%22%3A%7B%22pageIndex%22%3A10%2C%22rects%22%3A%5B%5B404.714%2C435.005%2C538.84%2C441.746%5D%2C%5B306.721%2C424.527%2C543.865%2C431.267%5D%2C%5B306.618%2C414.105%2C485.697%2C420.845%5D%5D%7D%2C%22citationItem%22%3A%7B%22uris%22%3A%5B%22http%3A%2F%2Fzotero.org%2Fusers%2F11261961%2Fitems%2F5N4VM3B9%22%5D%2C%22locator%22%3A%2211%22%7D%7D">“De acordo com nossa abordagem de análise baseada em IA, as três despesas orçamentárias mais essenciais que poderiam melhorar o PIB são gastos públicos, agricultura e subsídios.”</span> <span class="citation" data-citation="%7B%22citationItems%22%3A%5B%7B%22uris%22%3A%5B%22http%3A%2F%2Fzotero.org%2Fusers%2F11261961%2Fitems%2F5N4VM3B9%22%5D%2C%22locator%22%3A%2211%22%7D%5D%2C%22properties%22%3A%7B%7D%7D">(<span class="citation-item">Valle-Cruz et al., 2022, p. 11</span>)</span></p>
<p><span class="highlight" data-annotation="%7B%22attachmentURI%22%3A%22http%3A%2F%2Fzotero.org%2Fusers%2F11261961%2Fitems%2FK4FEFN2B%22%2C%22annotationKey%22%3A%22RIDYBYP8%22%2C%22color%22%3A%22%23ffd400%22%2C%22pageLabel%22%3A%2211%22%2C%22position%22%3A%7B%22pageIndex%22%3A10%2C%22rects%22%3A%5B%5B487.571%2C414.105%2C532.16%2C420.845%5D%2C%5B306.721%2C403.626%2C546.123%2C410.367%5D%2C%5B306.666%2C393.203%2C550.947%2C399.944%5D%2C%5B306.682%2C382.725%2C544.607%2C389.465%5D%2C%5B306.745%2C372.303%2C529.281%2C379.043%5D%2C%5B306.721%2C361.824%2C371.149%2C368.565%5D%5D%7D%2C%22citationItem%22%3A%7B%22uris%22%3A%5B%22http%3A%2F%2Fzotero.org%2Fusers%2F11261961%2Fitems%2F5N4VM3B9%22%5D%2C%22locator%22%3A%2211%22%7D%7D">“Esse achado é consistente com pesquisas anteriores que indicam que a agricultura e os gastos públicos têm um efeito significativo e positivo no PIB, e a saúde afeta diretamente a produtividade (Bhattarai, Lee, &amp; Park, 2014; Mogues, 2015; Ono, 2011). Além disso, descobrimos que os subsídios têm potencial para ativar a economia (Crescimento do PIB)”</span> <span class="citation" data-citation="%7B%22citationItems%22%3A%5B%7B%22uris%22%3A%5B%22http%3A%2F%2Fzotero.org%2Fusers%2F11261961%2Fitems%2F5N4VM3B9%22%5D%2C%22locator%22%3A%2211%22%7D%5D%2C%22properties%22%3A%7B%7D%7D">(<span class="citation-item">Valle-Cruz et al., 2022, p. 11</span>)</span></p>
