<p><span class="highlight" data-annotation="%7B%22attachmentURI%22%3A%22http%3A%2F%2Fzotero.org%2Fusers%2F11261961%2Fitems%2FK4FEFN2B%22%2C%22annotationKey%22%3A%22ZZDVNH2G%22%2C%22color%22%3A%22%23ffd400%22%2C%22pageLabel%22%3A%2211%22%2C%22position%22%3A%7B%22pageIndex%22%3A10%2C%22rects%22%3A%5B%5B306.49%2C267.741%2C547.017%2C274.481%5D%2C%5B306.721%2C257.318%2C532.648%2C264.059%5D%2C%5B306.61%2C246.84%2C530.649%2C253.581%5D%2C%5B306.721%2C236.418%2C523.636%2C243.158%5D%2C%5B306.618%2C225.939%2C549.416%2C232.68%5D%2C%5B306.761%2C215.516%2C539.065%2C222.257%5D%2C%5B306.634%2C205.038%2C552.782%2C211.778%5D%2C%5B306.618%2C194.704%2C550.913%2C201.445%5D%2C%5B306.721%2C184.138%2C449.468%2C190.879%5D%5D%7D%2C%22citationItem%22%3A%7B%22uris%22%3A%5B%22http%3A%2F%2Fzotero.org%2Fusers%2F11261961%2Fitems%2F5N4VM3B9%22%5D%2C%22locator%22%3A%2211%22%7D%7D">“De acordo com nossos resultados baseados na análise algorítmica inteligente, a desigualdade econômica, medida pelo índice de Gini, poderia ser abordada principalmente considerando políticas com foco em incentivo à educação e implementando estratégias para lidar com problemas de dívida pública e desemprego. Nesse sentido, o PIB mede a renda total, enquanto o índice de Gini mede a desigualdade de renda (Gastwirth, 1972). A redução da desigualdade poderia ser enfrentada com a geração de políticas de emprego que promovam um mercado de trabalho eficiente, produtivo e competente, o que gera a necessidade de gerar estratégias para apoiar o desemprego.”</span> <span class="citation" data-citation="%7B%22citationItems%22%3A%5B%7B%22uris%22%3A%5B%22http%3A%2F%2Fzotero.org%2Fusers%2F11261961%2Fitems%2F5N4VM3B9%22%5D%2C%22locator%22%3A%2211%22%7D%5D%2C%22properties%22%3A%7B%7D%7D">(<span class="citation-item">Valle-Cruz et al., 2022, p. 11</span>)</span></p>
