<p><span class="highlight" data-annotation="%7B%22attachmentURI%22%3A%22http%3A%2F%2Fzotero.org%2Fusers%2F11261961%2Fitems%2FK4FEFN2B%22%2C%22annotationKey%22%3A%222VNFEUMX%22%2C%22color%22%3A%22%23ffd400%22%2C%22pageLabel%22%3A%2212%22%2C%22position%22%3A%7B%22pageIndex%22%3A11%2C%22rects%22%3A%5B%5B463.952%2C583.245%2C547.495%2C589.985%5D%2C%5B306.53%2C572.822%2C544.799%2C579.562%5D%2C%5B306.666%2C562.343%2C541.18%2C569.084%5D%2C%5B306.921%2C551.921%2C403.568%2C558.662%5D%5D%7D%2C%22citationItem%22%3A%7B%22uris%22%3A%5B%22http%3A%2F%2Fzotero.org%2Fusers%2F11261961%2Fitems%2F5N4VM3B9%22%5D%2C%22locator%22%3A%2212%22%7D%7D">“Isso é consistente com uma abordagem algorítmica, pois os sistemas computacionais têm entradas que são processadas (despesas orçamentárias públicas) para gerar saídas (resultados econômicos, políticos e sociais).”</span></p>
